page.title: 15HOLSWORTHY WOOD PART 1
page.content: {Holsworthy Wood}was first planted in 1939 and covers 45 acres.A wood has stood in this area however for many years. { The varieties}of trees that are grown include,the Sitka Spruce,the Pine,the Beech and the Oak.{Conifers} are more widely grown than the decidous varieties. { }The{trees}are cut down when they are about 40-50 years old.Half of them are used for pallet boards and the others for chip boards,construction timber and stakes for fencing. There are many{animals}living in the wood including grey squirrels,badgers,foxes and many rodents.
